		<table width="100%">
		<tr>
			<td>
				<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="3"><b>    A Halfling Cleric's Guide for Levels 1 - 18</b></font>
					<br>
					<font face="verdana" size="2">
					<b><A href="mailto:altinure@hotmail.com">Teiggo Nubblet</a> | 
		            8/17/2001 6:05:41 PM</b></font></p>
		         <a href="guides.asp">
		         <font face="verdana" size="2">Return to guide listing.</font></a>
					
					<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="2">Hello everyone.<BR>
<BR>
If you're reading this guide, then you're probably interested in creating a Halfling Cleric.  This probably isn't the fastest guide, but this is where I hunted on my Cleric.  <BR>
<BR>
I love my Cleric, Teiggo, and he's definatly been my favorite character so far.  But being a Cleric isn't very easy, and you'll have to accept the fact that you'll be staring at your spell book 95% of the time, until level 35 when you don't need to look at it to med.  The results are rewarding though.  It's great just having to shout once that you're looking for a group and you get at least one tell asking for you to join their group.<BR>
<BR>
CHARACTER CREATION<BR>
<BR>
For my cleric, I added five to strength and twenty to wisdom.  This brought his strength up to 80 and his wisdom to 115.<BR>
<BR>
HUNTING GUIDE<BR>
<BR>
Levels 1 - 4 - <BR>
<BR>
For these first levels, run out to the Misty Thicket, by the bank, and kill everything that you can.  Sell everything!  You'll need the money for your level 5 spells.  I would also recommend buying a backpack when you get enough money.  This will really save you some time.  Keep hunting around the enterance to Rivervale until level 4.<BR>
<BR>
Once you get enough gold, you should buy your level 1 spells.<BR>
<BR>
Spells you should buy in order of importance at low levels...<BR>
<BR>
STRIKE - Use this spell to pull stuff at low levels.  It's very handy.<BR>
CURE POISON - This'll be useful when you start fighting giant spiders and snakes.<BR>
DIVINE AURA - KEEP THIS SPELL MEM'ED AT ALL TIMES!!!  You'll use this spell until you get your upgrade to Divine Aura around level 34.  It's VERY useful, mostly at high levels.  This spell gives you invulnerability for 18 seconds, which is just enough time usually for the tank to pull a MOB off you at higher levels.  This spell has saved my life numerous times.<BR>
<BR>
These were the only spells I used.  The other ones are pretty useless, but you can buy them if you want. :)<BR>
<BR>
Level 5 - 8 - <BR>
<BR>
At level 5, it's time to kill bigger things.  Run up the path in Misty Thicket until you reach a giant wall.  You'll be hunting beyond the wall from now on.  Once you get to the wall, take a right and run until you see a big hill.  A lot of large bats, giant rats, shadow wolves and large bears spawn on this hill.  You may need another person to take these on at level four, but I had no problems with them.  These should take you to level 5 pretty fast.<BR>
<BR>
Once you get to level five, it's time to buy some new spells.<BR>
<BR>
These are the spells I think you should buy in order of importance...<BR>
<BR>
LIGHT HEALING - This is your next healing spell.  You'll notice a big difference in the ammount you can heal, so buy it. :)<BR>
HOLY ARMOR - This is your first in the line of AC buffs.  Try to keep it on all your group members at all times.<BR>
FUROR - Another spell used to pull MOBs.<BR>
GATE - Returns you back to your bindspot.  Very useful when wanting to go home.<BR>
SUMMON DRINK - No more buying drinks.<BR>
CURE DISEASE - Useful when fighting undead or rabid animals.<BR>
WARD UNDEAD - A nice spell that does a lot of damage to undead monsters.<BR>
STUN - I've heard this spell can be useful is some situations at higher levels, not sure.  I bought it anyways.<BR>
<BR>
At level five, you can continue hunting on the big hill.  You should be able to solo everything there, but having a hunting partner doesn't hurt. :)<BR>
<BR>
For levels 6 through 8, start hunting giant bats and goblins.  You may need a group member to take them on, but it should take you to 8 pretty fast.<BR>
<BR>
Once you get 8, quickly run to the Cleric guild and put a point in meditate!  This is where you become a true cleric.  Now you will no longer need to tank, you'll just sit back and heal your group. :)<BR>
<BR>
Levels 8 - 10 - <BR>
<BR>
At level 8, it's time to leave Rivervale forever and head out to Freeport.  It's not too long of a journey, and it's a pretty easy one too.  I'd recommend going to www.eqatlas.com and getting maps to get there.<BR>
<BR>
Once you get to Freeport, run to the front gate and ask for a bind.  Most casters are willing to spare one and don't charge a thing.<BR>
<BR>
Once you get your bind, it's time to hunt orcs in a group in East Commons.  The loot here is AWSOME.  The only problem is it's hard to get in a group.  Once you find a group, your main goal is to heal.  Don't try to tank, just med and heal.  Even med through battles, only stand up when you need to heal.  If something gets on you, ask your group for help.  DO NOT run around screaming.  About once every five kills, an orc will drop a death fist slashed belt.  These sell for about 3pp per belt to players.  These are what will pay for your level 9 spells, so be sure to get some of these, just don't hyper-loot them.<BR>
<BR>
Level 9 means new spells again, and you should have enough pp to buy them.  If you don't, don't worry, just wait until you do.<BR>
<BR>
Spells that you should buy...<BR>
<BR>
CENTER - This is an upgrade to courage.  It's very useful, and should be kept on all members at all times.<BR>
ROOT - This spell is useful for when a MOB agros you, and your group doesn't have an enchanter.  Simply root the MOB, and move away.  Be sure to allert your group that you need help, or the MOB will just attack you again.<BR>
SUMMON FOOD - No more buying food.<BR>
ENDURE POISON AND FIRE - Useful when fighting monsters that cast spells or poison you<BR>
HAMMER OF WRATH - I didn't buy this spell, but it might be useful for you if you have a weapon yet.<BR>
INVIGOR - This spell gives the tank back stamina.  I've only had to use it a few times, but it's still useful.<BR>
FEAR - Useful if you ever want to fear/kite with a Druid at way higher levels. :)<BR>
<BR>
Keep hunting orcs until level 10.  You should get around 50pp from the orcs by the time you're 10.<BR>
<BR>
Levels 10 - 14 - <BR>
<BR>
Now it's time to head to North Ro to hunt Dervish Cutthroats in a group.  These aren't as great loot as orcs, but they're not bad.  These drop bronze weapons whihc can be sold for 1gp to 3pp to NPCs.  Use basically the same stratagy when fighting these as you did with orcs:  Med and heal.<BR>
<BR>
New spells at level 14, here are the spells which I think are most important...<BR>
<BR>
HEALING - This is a good healing spell, and you'll notice the improvement from Light Healing.<BR>
BIND AFFINITY - This is the spell that lets you create your own bind spot.<BR>
ENDURE COLD AND DISEASE - More spell resist spells.<BR>
INVISIBILITY VS. UNDEAD - This lets you be invisible to the undead, it's not too useful but still worth buying.<BR>
CANCEL MAGIC - Good for taking off damage shields off mobs.<BR>
SMITE - Your next DD spell<BR>
EXPULSE UNDEAD - Next in the line of Undead DD spells.<BR>
SYMBOL OF TRANSAL - A huge HP buff; although, I didn't use it much because it's expensive to cast at that level.<BR>
<BR>
Levels 14 - 18 -<BR>
<BR>
At level 14, you should head to the Oasis of Mar to hunt at orc highway.  Many people hate it here, but I had a lot of fun in this zone.  The things you should watch out for are Sand Giants and Spectres.  These roam around the Oasis, but I never had any problems with them.<BR>
<BR>
You should look for groups along orc highway.  This is good, fast exp, but the loot is horrible.  They rarely drop bronze weapons, so you never make any money.  Again, use the same stratagies for hunting as you have done since you were level 8:  Med and heal.<BR>
<BR>
CONCLUSION<BR>
<BR>
I hope my guide has helped you.  Once again, this isn't the fastest way to 18, but it's the way that worked for me.  I hope you've enjoyed your Cleric as much as I have.<BR>
<BR>
Teiggo Nubblet<BR>
Level 22 Halfling Cleric (7-15-01)<BR>
Tunare Server<BR>
<BR>
